%I A393485 #18 Mar 22 2026 22:43:22
%S A393485 6,12,120,8160,33553920
%N A393485 Areas of Heron triangles whose sides all have prime power lengths.
%H A393485 Florian Luca, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/3072343">Fermat Primes and Heron Triangles with Prime Power Sides</a>, Amer. Math. Monthly, 110 (No. 1, 2003), pp. 46-49.
%F A393485 For n >= 2, a(n) = 2*(A019434(n) - 2)*(A019434(n-1) - 1).
%e A393485 a(1) is the area of the Heron triangle with side lengths that are all prime powers: 3, 4, and 5.
%e A393485 a(2) is the area of the Heron triangle with side lengths that are all prime powers: 5, 5, and 8.
%o A393485 (Magma) lst:=[6]; for n in [2..5] do if IsPrime(2^(2^(n-1))+1) then Append(~lst, 2*(2^(2^n/2)-1)*(2^(2^n/4))); end if; end for; lst;
%Y A393485 Cf. A019434, A221837.
%K A393485 nonn,hard,more
%O A393485 1,1
%A A393485 _Arkadiusz Wesolowski_, Mar 16 2026
